"title": "8799: polytheism",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8799",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Belief in, and worship of, more than one god. It is forbidden in Scripture because God has revealed himself as the one true God. Israel in the OT and the church in the NT lived amongst polytheistic peoples. The Israelites shared in this worship and so came under God's judgment.</p>\n<h2>The uniqueness of God</h2>\n<h3>There is only one true God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:5-Isa45:6\">ISA 45:5–45:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:4\">DEU 6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:39\">DEU 32:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:10\">ISA 43:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:8\">ISA 44:8</a></p>\n<h3>The contrast of the true God with idols</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:9\">1TH 1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:26\">1CH 16:26</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:5\">PSA 96:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:18-Isa40:19\">ISA 40:18–40:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:25-Isa40:26\">ISA 40:25–40:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:29\">ACT 17:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:4-1Cor8:6\">1CO 8:4–8:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:8\">GAL 4:8</a></p>\n<h2>Polytheism is expressly forbidden</h2>\n<h3>Warnings against worshipping idols</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:23\">EXO 20:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:3-Exod20:5\">EXO 20:3–20:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:7-Deut5:9\">DEU 5:7–5:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:13\">EXO 23:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:7\">LEV 17:7</a></p>\n<h3>Polytheism compromises relationship with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:35-2Kgs17:38\">2KI 17:35–17:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:16\">DEU 31:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:10\">JER 11:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:18-1Cor10:22\">1CO 10:18–10:22</a></p>\n<h3>The challenge to Israel to worship God only</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:15\">JOS 24:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:2-Gen35:4\">GEN 35:2–35:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:2-Deut12:4\">DEU 12:2–12:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:21\">1KI 18:21</a></p>\n<h2>Polytheism brings God's judgment</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:20\">EXO 22:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:17-Deut31:18\">DEU 31:17–31:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:16\">JOS 23:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:11-Jer11:13\">JER 11:11–11:13</a></p>\n<h2>Polytheism among Israel's neighbours</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:6\">JDG 10:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:23\">JDG 16:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:33\">1KI 11:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:2\">2KI 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:29-2Kgs17:33\">2KI 17:29–17:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:1\">ISA 46:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:2\">JER 50:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:14\">EZK 8:14</a></p>\n<h2>Polytheism among the Israelites</h2>\n<h3>They were called to destroy foreign gods</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:51-Num33:52\">NUM 33:51–33:52</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:24\">EXO 23:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:12-Exod34:13\">EXO 34:12–34:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:2-Deut12:3\">DEU 12:2–12:3</a></p>\n<h3>They were seduced by foreign gods</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:15-2Kgs17:18\">2KI 17:15–17:18</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:11\">JER 2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:15-Exod34:16\">EXO 34:15–34:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num25:2\">NUM 25:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:30\">DEU 12:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:16-Deut32:17\">DEU 32:16–32:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:11-Judg2:13\">JDG 2:11–2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:34-Ps106:36\">PSA 106:34–106:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:13\">HOS 2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:2\">HOS 11:2</a></p>\n<h3>Polytheism among Israel's kings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:5-1Kgs11:7\">1KI 11:5–11:7</a> <em>Solomon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:28-1Kgs12:29\">1KI 12:28–12:29</a> <em>Jeroboam, king of Israel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:30-1Kgs16:33\">1KI 16:30–16:33</a> <em>Ahab, king of Israel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:3-2Kgs16:4\">2KI 16:3–16:4</a> <em>Ahaz, king of Judah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:3-2Kgs21:5\">2KI 21:3–21:5</a> <em>Manasseh, king of Judah</em></p>\n<h3>Examples of reforming kings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:12-1Kgs15:13\">1KI 15:12–15:13</a> <em>Asa, king of Judah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:4\">2KI 18:4</a> <em>Hezekiah, king of Judah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:12-2Kgs23:15\">2KI 23:12–23:15</a> <em>Josiah, king of Judah</em></p>\n<h2>The character of polytheism in the OT</h2>\n<h3>The physical representation of deities</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:1\">LEV 26:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:23\">1KI 14:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:5\">ISA 48:5</a></p>\n<h3>Cult prostitution</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:17\">DEU 23:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:24\">1KI 14:24</a></p>\n<h3>Human sacrifice</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:21\">LEV 18:21</a> <em>to Molech</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:31\">DEU 12:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:26-2Kgs3:27\">2KI 3:26–3:27</a> <em>to Chemosh</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:5\">JER 19:5</a> <em>to Baal</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:20-Ezek16:21\">EZK 16:20–16:21</a></p>\n<h3>Self-mutilation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:28-1Kgs18:29\">1KI 18:28–18:29</a></p>\n<h2>Polytheism in the NT</h2>\n<h3>It was widespread</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:23\">ACT 17:23</a></strong> <em>The Athenians were fearful of offending a god by failing to give him attention. Any omissions were covered in the designation “UNKNOWN GOD”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:11-Acts14:13\">ACT 14:11–14:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:35\">ACT 19:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:5-1Cor8:6\">1CO 8:5–8:6</a></p>\n<h3>The worship of man-made idols</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:2\">1CO 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:16\">ACT 17:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:26\">ACT 19:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:20-Rom1:23\">ROM 1:20–1:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:19-1Cor10:20\">1CO 10:19–10:20</a> <em>Idols in themselves are nothing, but they represent a demonic presence which lies behind polytheistic worship.</em></p>",
